    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="835"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d835">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/998</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dorsey</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="69" xml:id="d835fn69">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Minister in his despatch No. 2388, October 21; received November 22,
                        1929.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-21">October 21,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg leave to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatch No. 340, of October 15, 1929,<note n="70" xml:id="d835fn70">Not
                        printed.</note> in which you inform the Legation that the Goods Tax now
                    being collected at Tsingtao is the same as that referred to by the American
                    Consul at Tsinan as the Shantung Provincial Consolidated Goods Tax, and in which
                    you inquire whether or not a protest should be entered with the local
                    authorities in view of the discriminatory features of the tax. Since the
                    provisions of this tax appear to be clearly discriminatory, you are instructed
                    to lodge a protest on these grounds with the local authorities.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. V. A. MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
